title: VOLLEYBALL: Morrice beats Byron in five
text:
AVERI MUNRO of Morrice goes for a kill against Byron Tuesday at Byron High School. Argus-Press Photo/Jerome Murphy Parker Viele, Morgan Spencer, Averi Munro, Sophia Ruff 
BYRON’S PARKER VIELE, left, makes a tip as Morrice players Morgan Spencer (15) and Averi Munro, far right, try to block Tuesday at Byron. Also shown is Byron’s Sophia Ruff. Argus-Press Photo/Jerome Murphy Maddie Lewis, Hannah Hedger, Chelsea Featherstone, Morgan Childers 
MORRICE’S MADDIE LEWIS (16) makes a set as teammate Hannah Hedger, right, looks on. Defending for Byron are Chelsea Featherstone, left, and Morgan Childers (1). Argus-Press Photo/Jerome Murphy Hannah Hedger, Maddie Lewis, Kortnie O'Connor 
MORRICE SETTER Hannah Hedger (12) lofts a set to a teammate against Byron Tuesday as Orioles Maddie Lewis, left, and Kortnie O’Connor, right, look on at Byron High School. Argus-Press Photo/Jerome Murphy Maddie Lewis, Sophia Ruff, Morgan Childers 
MORRICE’S MADDIE LEWIS, right, makes a volley as Byron defenders Sophia Ruff (14) and Morgan Childers (1) look on Tuesday at Byron. Posted: Wednesday, October 21, 2015 11:10 am VOLLEYBALL: Morrice beats Byron in five By JEROME MURPHY Argus-Press Sports Writer The Argus-Press | 0 comments 
BYRON — Averi Munro had nine kills and 21 digs and Kortnie O’Connor added four aces and 24 digs to help Morrice hold off Byron in five games Tuesday. 
The Orioles won the first two games — 25-18, 25-17 — before the host Eagles won the next two, 25-17, 25-22.
